> 
>    As some of you may have heard, I'm currently rewritting CalChart.  If 
> you've never used CalChart before, go ahead and delete this.  But if you 
> have any dislikes about the current version and want to offer 
> suggestions, read on.  That said, here are some things that I'll 
> definately implement:
[...]
>    * Shows saved in a single file- save disk space as well.

I would think that keeping stunt sheets as separate files has its
advantages.  Mainly, if things go wrong or you accidentally delete
a sheet or something else, most network programs will keep around
your deleted files, so you can recreate whatever you deleted.  When
you just modify a big file it becomes much easier to simply corrupt
the file, and restoring a small change becomes nasty.
[...]
>    Finally, some things already suggested that may not get done:
>    * Play MIDI files along with the show (not feasible until the band 
>        gets a sound card in the computers)

Which will not happen until we move to a different OS (like OS/2
or maybe Win95 [or 96 or...]) since running a sound card AND network
software is practically impossible...
[...]
> Gurk

Rune

