Does your new print routine deal with Spring show format?  If not, I would
highly suggest that you stop your current project temporarily and shift
to the printing program.  Right now, it is a fairly high priority to be
able to make decent spring show sheets without having to cut and paste
like we've been doing for the last two years.

Take a look at the harmon ss sheets from the early part of this decade (91
or 92).  They might give you some good ideas.  In particular, notice how
the walls of harmon are printed on the sheets around the grid.  I think
that this is a good idea.  The shape of the stage should definitely be
reflected on the sheets, especially since the grid is actually slightly
larger than the stage.  See if you can get into Zellerbach to take some
measurements.  Or maybe they will be able to give them to you.  Be aware
of the fact that the front of the stage is not straight.

