Just have a prompt for saving when the user quits.  This is a pretty
standard feature on word processors and text editors.
 
> As far as having non-animated stuntsheets, I'm quite sure why you can't 
> just remove the sheets from the Animate group.  In view of efficiency, 
> you'd probably have to actually implement it by toggling a flag for each 
> stuntsheet, but you could give the user the illusion that it's a group.

I had discarded the notion of collections and groups with respect to
animation, but this is a good idea.  I know that this makes your
job a little harder, but how about having an Animation collection?  Each
section of this collection represents the men that will be displayed on
that stuntsheet.  If you don't want a stuntsheet to appear in the
animation at all, then make its section empty.  

If you only want one part of a flow to be animated, just set the section
to be the men that you want.  This could be a useful tool in analyzing
flows.  It is essentially like highlighting men in the animation, except
that rather than making the men orange to stand out, you make them invisible.

Dan


