> Yes, but it doesn't do this at the moment.  However, there are avantages 
> to having all stuntsheets look consistent, like conherency when flipping 
> through all the stuntsheets.

I understood that the current printing routine doesn't handle automatic
size adjustment, but then again, there's probably many things that it
doesn't yet do....

I don't think it is too important to worry about stuntsheets changing
sizes constantly.  I certainly agree that consistency in size is extremely
useful.  I always flipped back and forth between pages, and it made things
very convenient to be able to look in the same location on both pages. 
However, the idea is to shrink the scale ONLY when placing points off the
field.  This is only going to happen very rarely, and then it will be some
bizarre thing where half the band is off the field.  There's nothing wrong
with printing one stuntsheet per year at a different size. 
 
