> I fixed that bug in loading shows.  It also has some more sanity checks, so 
> hopefully random bugs will give an error message instead of seg 
> faulting.  The problem was basically that the standard C library in SunOS 
> doesn't handle DOS-style ASCII text.  The fix was pretty minor.  For the 
> new format, there was also a small, stupid bug.  A new version of wxWindows 
> was released, so I've incorporated that also.  This might fix some bugs.  
> I've also put wxhelp on the web page, so you can try it out.  I've only 
> put the XView version on there because it's smaller than the Motif 
> binary, but it will work with either version.

Loading shows works now.

Am I supposed to do something to the wxhelp file before using it?  When I
click on the help menu item, I get the following messages in my shell
window: 

	./wxhelp: syntax error at line 1: `(' unexpected
	select in wxSleep: Interrupted system call

After playing around with both versions, I have decided that I prefer the
motif version to the xview version.  I don't know why exactly; it just has
a more comfortable feel to me.  However, I will continue to test whatever 
you want me to.

Dan


