So, adding CalChart to the standard Band program manager and trying to
figure out how to best configure it I have these suggestions/questions:

Is there a way to specify the default data directory?  In order to 
get it to read the configuration file I had to make the default 
directory S:\CALCHART, which then means that they get dropped into
S:\CALCHART when they want to open a file or save a file or whatever,
which is a lot more confusing then getting dropped into some standard
place where they actually have write permissions  :-)  Is there a 
way currently to do this?  Make the program and config file be in
the S:\CALCHART, and then have the default data directory someplace
like G:\ or U:\ or R:\?  How about even a little more complicated--
Program is in S:\CALCHART, config file is in U:\, standard data
directory is G:\CALCHART.  Is this possible?  How about with a
command line option giving the config file location (this is how
a lot of other Windoze programs do it).

Anyway, that's my question.

Talk to you soon.

Rune


