> I've finally figured out a solution to editing text in calchart.  It's 
> going to be very difficult to make edits take effect immediately, so it 
> only copies the text from the window to the actually internals when you 
> try to read the text.  I've implemented the show description windows 
> now.  So if you try to save the show, or open another description window, 
> the changes are copied.  If you want, you can try out the latest 
> version.  Try opening multiple description windows and watch the * 
> indicating a modified show.  Please let me know if you think this will be 
> confusing to people.

After grabbing XKeysymDB, everything seems to work perfectly.

Here is an initial list of comments.  Many more to come over the next few 
days.  Except for the first three, they all pertain to the show info window.

1)  I had trouble unzipping the archived shows.  unzip responds with 
"Unknown compression method".

2)  When I try to use help, I get error messages because wxhelp is not 
available.  After two 15-second attempts, it gives up.  This is basically 
fine, but I was wondering if there is a way to abort the process so that 
you don't have to wait for 30 seconds before you regain control.

3)  Changing the zoom size causes the screen to be refreshed twice.  I 
think that this is a result of the way that you fixed a previous bug that 
I mentioned.  Anyway, this is generally inefficient and annoying.  Also, 
sometimes there is a significant delay of several seconds between the 
first and second refresh.

4)  I am much less confused by the "set labels" and "set num points" 
buttons.  Did you change something?  I don't remember how it was.

5)  Why is there a scroll bar underneath the letters?

6)  Same thing about "not enough labels defined".  I know it's not that 
important, but still worth mentioning.

7)  When you open the window, the cursor in the comments window appears 
at the end of the text.  Should the cursor appear at the beginning of the 
text?  I'm not sure what is the convention.

8)  Funny things still happen to the dotted line when you scroll through 
the letters.  We already discussed this and you blamed it on a bug in 
some standard library, but I don't accept excuses! 

9)  Is there a way to (de)select blocks of letters?  Or all letters?  If 
not, there should be.

10)  We had discussed the ambiguity in the name "Show info...."  I 
propose "Information" as the name of the window.

11) I see that you have made great progress in dealing with more than one 
"Information" window open at once.  The number of points and the 
points-per-letter are transferred correctly; that is, when you implement 
the change, the other windows change accordingly.

However, the comments do not get updated.  I see two ways around this, 
but I'm not sure if either is doable.  First, you could have the comments 
appear only in the first "Information" window; all the rest wouldn't even 
have a field for comments.  Second, you could transfer changes from the 
first window to the second when you select the comments field of the 
second. 

Which version of the comments gets stored as the official version when 
you close all the windows?  It seems arbitrary to me.

There are some very strange things going on with the selected letters for 
labels.  When you set labels in one window, the other window gets updated 
in a completely bizarre manner.  I can't even figure out what is 
happenning, let alone why.

12) (De)selecting letters does not get "remembered" after closing and 
reopening unless you clicked on "set labels".  Is this the way it should 
be?  I guess so.

Dan



