Here is a list of things that I have tinkered with:

	Show info...
	Zoom
	label flips
	symbol changes
	Copy sheet before
	Copy sheet after
	Set beats...
	Set title...
	Grid
	some of the Animation

Things that I have yet to tinker with:

	file loading, saving, etc.
	Some of the animation
	Continuity editing
	Bizarre things with moving men
	Multiple windows of various sorts

I am limited by the fact that I can't get any of the archived shows to
unzip.  If I had something to work with, it would be a lot easier.

Last night, I had a bright idea about making circles.  Gridsize is a way
of restricting destinations of individualmoves to a certain set of points.
There could be an option to restrict destinations to the points on a circle
with a given center and a given radius.  There could even be a suboption to
restrict further to N evenly spaced points around the circle.  I imagine
this being implemented as a "Circle..." option on the grid menu.  I believe
that this will be a significant aid to users.

Come to think of it, this might be generalizable to other kinds of curves,
but I think that could wait for Version 3.1.


Here are a whole bunch of comments.  More will come tomorrow or on Thursday.

1)  In general, there is too much screen refreshing.  It is both slow and
annoying.  Martin dealt with this problem effectively by refreshing locally.
Is this possible?

2)  The *.shw and *.mas inconsistency for default names is still present.

3)  Moving the zoom slide and returning it to its original position causes an
unnecessary refresh.

4)  The label font seems a little bit too big.  Three-digit labels should be
easily readable at two-step spacing.  Right now, it looks like 141, 151, 161,
..., instead of 114, 115, 116, etc.

5)  I am very pleased with the snap-to-grid for moving.  It makes 1step
locating much easier because you can count the jumps from a corner.  It also
makes low zooms actually useful for more than just overviewing.

6)  A zoom change always returns the view to the SW corner of the field.
I think the center point of the view should be preserved under change of zoom,
unless the entire field will fit into the view in which case the field should
be located in the upper left corner of the view.

7)  Label flips works perfectly.

8)  Lassoing should NOT snap to grid, no matter what the grid setting.

9)  Aren't "plain slash men" usually called just "slashmen"?  Regardless, the
band's convention should be what you use.  This is important for the help bar
at the bottom of the window.

10) When you make a new sheet, the name of a sheet gets copied from the
previous one.
I remember we had a very long discussion about an auto-naming scheme.  What
happenned to that idea?

11) Probably a good idea to ask for verification before deleting a sheet.

12) I think that "Copy sheet before (resp. after)" should be called "Insert
sheet before (resp. after)".

13) Long long names push the sheet number and the "*" offscreen.  How about
a maximum of 32 characters or so?

14) "1 beats".  Is there a way to improve the grammar?
but you and I think like computer scientists.  I'm not sure if itbut you and I think like computer scientists.  I'm not sure if it
15) Blockmoves should not snap all the men to grid, just the "leading" man.

16) In animation window, the sheet number (i.e., "1 of 20") should be
displayed as well as the beat number and the sheet name.

17) Your convention is to show the zeroth beat of a sheet as opposed to
showing the 16th (or whateverth) beat of a sheet.  I think this makes sense
because it agrees with the way that musicians talk about beats.  However,
it is a change from the conventions of version 2.  I'm just pointing out
the difference and that your convention really is an arbitrary decision.

18) In most applications, the last sheet has 0 beats.  However, sometimes
it has beats.  If the last sheet has 16 beats, then the animator will only
go up to 15; you need to add an extra click of animation for the "close".

19) The animation window should have a reverse play button, a jump-to-sheet
option, a jump-to-end, and a jump-to-beginning.  Come to think of it, the
latter three ought to be available in the main window, too.

20) In the animation window, previous-stuntsheet should take you to the
beginning of the current sheet if you are not at the zeroth beat.  Think
about how a CD player works.




